criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Above 18 years old

          -  Have paraplegia as a result of a spinal cord injury morn than one year;

          -  Able to perform push-ups independently and raise the arm above the head;

          -  Self-propel a manual wheelchair as the primary means of mobility

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Have history of fractures or dislocations in the shoulder, elbow, or wrist from which
             you have not fully recovered;

          -  Have upper limb pain as a result of a complex regional pain syndrome;

          -  Have a implant or pacemaker within the torso or upper arm;

          -  Pregnant female.
